.SH SlepianCoeffsToSH
Convert a function expressed in Slepian coefficients to spherical
harmonic coefficients.
.SH Usage
call SlepianCoeffsToSH(\f[CR]film\f[R], \f[CR]falpha\f[R],
\f[CR]galpha\f[R], \f[CR]lmax\f[R], \f[CR]nmax\f[R],
\f[CR]exitstatus\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]film\f[R] : output, real(dp), dimension (2, \f[CR]lmax\f[R]+1, \f[CR]lmax\f[R]+1)
The spherical harmonic coefficients of the global function.
.TP
\f[CR]falpha\f[R] : input, real(dp), dimension (\f[CR]nmax\f[R])
A vector containing the Slepian coefficients of the function.
.TP
\f[CR]galpha\f[R] : input, real(dp), dimension ((\f[CR]lmax\f[R]+1)**2, \f[CR]nmax\f[R])
An array containing the spherical harmonic coefficients of the Slepian
functions.
Each column corresponds to a single function of which the spherical
harmonic coefficients can be unpacked with \f[CR]SHVectorToCilm\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]lmax\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The spherical harmonic bandwidth of the Slepian functions.
.TP
\f[CR]nmax\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The number of expansion coefficients to compute.
This must be less than or equal to (\f[CR]lmax\f[R]+1)**2.
.TP
\f[CR]exitstatus\f[R] : output, optional, integer(int32)
If present, instead of executing a STOP when an error is encountered,
